Hardee Power Partners Limited Market-Base Sales Tariff FERC Electric Tariff No. 1
1. Availability: Hardee Power Partners Limited (???HPP??? or ???Seller???) makes electric capacity and/or energy available under this Market-Based Sales Tariff (???Tariff???) for sales at wholesale to purchasers with whom HPP, at its discretion, contracts.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric capacity and/or energy at wholesale by HPP that are not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule.
3. Rates. All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and HPP.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and HPP.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller???s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller???s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller???s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. (a) In MEP Investments, ITF LLC, et al., 87 FERC ??61,209, Appendix B at 61,830 (1999), the Commission granted HPP the following waivers and blanket authorization: (i) Waiver of the accounting, reporting, and other requirements of 18 C.F.R. Parts 41 (accounts, records, and memorandum), 101 (uniform system of accounts) and 141 (statement and reports); (ii) Waiver of the reporting requirements of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission???s regulations, except Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; and (iii) Blanket authorization under 18 C.F.R. Part 34 of all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. (b) In Hardee Power Partners Ltd., et al., 114 FERC ?? 61,131, at PP 13 and 16 (2006), the Commission granted HPP waivers of the Commission???s open access transmission requirements under Section 35.28, Part 37 and Part 358 of the Commission???s regulations. 7. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR ?? 35.36(a), in the Southwest, Northeast, Southwest Power Pool, Central, and Northwest Regions and Seller is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?? 35.36(a), in the Southeast Region.
